<figureCitation box="[309,389,1393,1418]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="70.[151,250,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[169,1419,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@70.[168,1420,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURE 38. Bradycalanus abyssicolus n. sp. female antennule ancestral segments: A, segments I – IX; B, segments X – XVI; C, segments XVII – XXI; D, segments XXII – XXVIII; E, reduced setae of segment I; F, hair sensillum on dorsal surface of segment III. Mouthparts: G, antenna; H, mandibular palp. Scale bars represent 1.0 mm on figures A – D; 0.1 mm on remaining figures. Illustrated specimen from ANDEEP II, ANTXIX / 4, Stn 135 - 4." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/311019/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
